answers.body_markdown:
To avoid reading and storing all input bytes in memory you can use [`InputStream.transerTo(OutputStream)`][1] method:

```
try (var in = CreateYourInputStreamHere;
     var out = CreateYourOutputStreamHere) {
  in.transferTo(out);
}
```

In Java 17 this approach will use a 8K buffer, reading and writing a single 8K chunk of data before processing next chunk.


  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/io/InputStream.html#transferTo(java.io.OutputStream)

