I was able to find the answer on at [SeleniumHQ issues][1]. Essentially, CapabilityType.LOGGING_PREFS is broken in this version of ChromeDriver. I changed the line

    options.setCapability(CapabilityType.LOGGING_PREFS, logPrefs);

to

    options.setCapability(&quot;goog:loggingPrefs&quot;, logPrefs);

 the preference name was changed to goog:loggingPrefs to be W3C compliant. I was able to collect network logs after this change. 


